## Problema 1 <a name="1"></a>
**Enunciado:**
Diseñar etapas
amplificadoras
para adaptar:

a)
$$V_{in} (0, 0.1\text{ V})$$
$$\to$$
$$V_{out} (-5, +5\text{ V})$$

b)
$$V_{in} (-0.2, 0.5\text{ V})$$
$$\to$$
$$V_{out} (0, 10\text{ V})$$

c)
$$V_{in} (1, 1.5\text{ V})$$
$$\to$$
$$V_{out} (+1, -1\text{ V})$$

d)
$$V_{in} (0, 0.01\text{ V})$$
$$\to$$
$$V_{out} (-10, +10\text{ V})$$

**Solución:**
1. Ecuaciones:
$$V_{out} = A \cdot V_{in} + B$$

a)
$$-5 = A \cdot 0 + B$$
$$+5 = A \cdot 0.1 + B$$
$$\implies B = -5$$
$$\text{V}$$
$$\implies A = 100$$
$$V_{out} = 100 \cdot V_{in} - 5$$

b)
$$0 = A \cdot (-0.2) + B$$
$$10 = A \cdot 0.5 + B$$
$$\implies A = 14.29$$
$$\implies B = 2.86$$
$$\text{V}$$
$$V_{out} = 14.29 \cdot V_{in} + 2.86$$

c)
$$1 = A \cdot 1 + B$$
$$-1 = A \cdot 1.5 + B$$
$$\implies A = -4$$
$$\implies B = 5$$
$$\text{V}$$
$$V_{out} = -4 \cdot V_{in} + 5$$

d)
$$-10 = A \cdot 0 + B$$
$$+10 = A \cdot 0.01 + B$$
$$\implies B = -10$$
$$\text{V}$$
$$\implies A = 2000$$
$$V_{out} = 2000 \cdot V_{in} - 10$$

2. Diseño (ej. a)
Montaje de dos
etapas
inversoras:
$$V_{out} = \frac{R_3 R_5}{R_1 R_4} V_{in} - \frac{R_5}{R_2} V_{ref}$$
Para:
$$V_{ref} = 5$$
$$\text{V}$$
Elegimos:
$$R_1 = R_4 = 10$$
$$\text{k}\Omega$$
$$R_3 = R_5 = 100$$
$$\text{k}\Omega$$
$$R_2 = 100$$
$$\text{k}\Omega$$

